comment: This is a great easy drinking flavored whiskey. Love the nuttiness and the peach notes. Best drank over ice!
Rich flavor. Sweet. Taste just like a peach ring, great sipping whisky as well
No thanks. Very artificial tasting. Might be good to mix with Peach Snapple.
Very sweet but true to the flavors, very good.
Hard pass. Tastes like balls and chemical sadness.
Smooth but j hope you really like pecan!
My babysitter bought me a bottle of this, couldn't help but drink the hole bottle and drive to get another one. Also, Florida Georgia Line is probably my fav artist
good. very sweet.  tastes like the honey a bit.
Not bad, interesting twist. But a tad too sweet.
Way too sweet. Basically "whiskey" syrup for pancakes.
More peach then pecan flavor.  More of a summertime drink than fall.
Now that’s a shooting whiskey.  Flavor is right on; peach and pecan with some syrupy sweetness.  Not for sipping but good for shooting and probably makes a mean mixed drink.

Oaky color with a hint of orange. The peach really comes through in the aroma. The peach also is the dominant flavor and slightly sweet. There are some nutty notes, but hard to identify them as pecan. Nice mouth feel. The peach really lingers. Overall pleasant. Would be really nice in the summer when you’re looking for something fruity.
Definite light peach and then the pecan. Easy sipper for sure.
I dont like the flavor of it. Really syrup like.
